Preheat oven to 425. Halve, peel, and dice the @yellow onion{1}(peeled and diced). Remove the ribs and stems from the @collard greens{1%bunch} and thinly slice. Slice the corn kernels off the @corn on the cob{1}. Mince the @jalapeño{1}(ribs and seeds removed if you prefer less heat).

Heat @olive oil{1/2%tbsp} in a medium #oven-proof pan{} over medium heat. Add the onion and cook, tossing, for ~{5%minutes}, until softened. Meanwhile, mince the @garlic{2%cloves}(minced). Add the jalapeño and corn to the pan and cook ~{1-2%minutes} more. Reserve half this mixture in a medium #bowl{} to the side.

Add the @ground pork{8%oz} and garlic to the pan and cook, breaking up the pieces, ~{4-5%minutes}, until browned and cooked through. Add @water{1/2%cup} and the @veggie stock concentrate{1} to the pan and stir to combine. Add the collard greens and @white wine vinegar{2%tsp} to the pan and cook until wilted, ~{2-3%minutes}.

> If you don't have an oven-proof pan, transfer this mixture into a small baking dish.

Add half the @cornbread mix{1%pack} to the bowl with the reserved vegetable mixture. Stir in the @sour cream{4%tbsp} and @water{3%tbsp} until just combined. Spoon this batter over the pork mixture and place pan in the oven for ~{15-20%minutes}, until cornbread is browned and cooked through.

Scoop cornbread pie into bowls and enjoy!